                    <span>For me, No More Drama was a great book!! I don't see how anyone could not like the first book, Drama Queen, because it was one of the most entertaining books I have ever read in my life. No More Drama was an awesome read too. The story line was easy to follow and the characters were the same as in Drama Queen if you read the book from cover to cover. I loved it!!!
<br />For the reviewer "Miss T", if you didn't like the first book, why did you bother to read the second. As far as La Jill Hunt's writing skills, they must not be too bad because she's still making dough selling books and according to the other reviews, has fans for life - myself included. From reading your review, I think you have some type of personal beef with the writer (which is what a lot of immature people do these days on the review sites)and you're just giving her more drama to write about. I look forward to your next book, La Jill. As an Essence Best-Seller myself, I know you got skills!!! </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">fooled me 1 2 many times</div>
